apabilities, AI-powered search, visual mind mapping, tagging systems, and integrations. Now let me continue with the implementation roadmap and technical details by adding more comprehensive sections to complete the specification document: Using Tool | Doc Edit Let me check the current content of the document to see what sections have been generated: Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 800,900 Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 1200,1495 Perfect! Now I need to add the missing Implementation Roadmap section that was referenced in the table of contents. Let me insert it in the right place: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -1070,6 +1070,158 @@     </table> <div class=\"section-break\"> +      <h2>9. Implementation Roadmap & Milestones</h2> +    </div> + +    <h3>9.1 Development Phases</h3> +    <div class=\"spec-box\"> +      <h4>Phase 1: Foundation (Months 1-3)</h4> +      <ul> +        <li>Core data models and database setup</li> +        <li>Basic authentication and user management</li> +        <li>File upload and processing pipeline</li> +        <li>Simple search functionality</li> +        <li><strong>Deliverable:</strong> MVP with basic CRUD operations</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Phase 2: AI Integration (Months 4-6)</h4> +      <ul> +        <li>AI-powered content analysis and tagging</li> +        <li>Semantic search implementation</li> +        <li>Basic knowledge graph construction</li> +        <li>Memory system foundation</li> +        <li><strong>Deliverable:</strong> AI-powered search and tagging system</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Phase 3: Visualization (Months 7-9)</h4> +      <ul> +        <li>Infinite canvas development</li> +        <li>Interactive mind mapping tools</li> +        <li>Knowledge graph visualization</li> +        <li>Advanced filtering and organization</li> +        <li><strong>Deliverable:</strong> Visual knowledge mapping interface</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Phase 4: Collaboration (Months 10-12)</h4> +      <ul> +        <li>Team features and sharing</li> +        <li>Real-time collaboration</li> +        <li>Advanced integrations</li> +        <li>Performance optimization</li> +        <li><strong>Deliverable:</strong> Full-featured collaborative platform</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + +    <h3>9.2 Sprint Planning</h3> +    <table> +      <tr> +        <th>Sprint</th> +        <th>Duration</th> +        <th>Key Features</th> +        <th>Success Metrics</th> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 1-2</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>Project setup, basic UI, user authentication</td> +        <td>User registration and login working</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 3-4</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>File upload, basic content processing</td> +        <td>Users can upload and view documents</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 5-6</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>Search functionality, basic tagging</td> +        <td>Search returns relevant results</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 7-8</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>AI integration, semantic search</td> +        <td>AI-powered search with 80%+ accuracy</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 9-10</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>Knowledge graph visualization</td> +        <td>Interactive graph with 1000+ nodes</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Sprint 11-12</td> +        <td>4 weeks</td> +        <td>Mind mapping canvas, infinite scroll</td> +        <td>Smooth 60fps interactions</td> +      </tr> +    </table> + +    <h3>9.3 Resource Requirements</h3> +    <div class=\"spec-box\"> +      <h4>Team Composition</h4> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Project Manager:</strong> 1 FTE - Overall coordination and delivery</li> +        <li><strong>Frontend Developers:</strong> 2 FTE - React/TypeScript specialists</li> +        <li><strong>Backend Developers:</strong> 2 FTE - Node.js/Python expertise</li> +        <li><strong>AI/ML Engineer:</strong> 1 FTE - LLM integration and optimization</li> +        <li><strong>UI/UX Designer:</strong> 1 FTE - Interface design and user experience</li> +        <li><strong>DevOps Engineer:</strong> 0.5 FTE - Infrastructure and deployment</li> +        <li><strong>QA Engineer:</strong> 1 FTE - Testing and quality assurance</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Budget Estimates</h4> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Development Team:</strong> $1.2M annually</li> +        <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> $50K annually (cloud services, APIs)</li> +        <li><strong>AI Services:</strong> $100K annually (OpenAI, Claude, embeddings)</li> +        <li><strong>Tools & Licenses:</strong> $25K annually</li> +        <li><strong>Total Year 1:</strong> $1.375M</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + +    <h3>9.4 Risk Assessment & Mitigation</h3> +    <table> +      <tr> +        <th>Risk</th> +        <th>Probability</th> +        <th>Impact</th> +        <th>Mitigation Strategy</th> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>AI API rate limits/costs</td> +        <td>High</td> +        <td>Medium</td> +        <td>Implement caching, use multiple providers, optimize prompts</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Performance with large datasets</td> +        <td>Medium</td> +        <td>High</td> +        <td>Implement pagination, lazy loading, optimize queries</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>EasySite.ai platform limitations</td> +        <td>Medium</td> +        <td>High</td> +        <td>Design modular architecture, have migration plan</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>User adoption challenges</td> +        <td>Medium</td> +        <td>High</td> +        <td>Focus on UX, implement onboarding, gather feedback</td> +      </tr> +      <tr> +        <td>Data privacy/security issues</td> +        <td>Low</td> +        <td>Very High</td> +        <td>Implement strong encryption, regular audits, compliance</td> +      </tr> +    </table> + +    <div class=\"section-break\"> <h2>10. Technical Stack Recommendations</h2> </div> Now let me create a comprehensive visual mind map to accompany this specification document: Using Tool | Programmatic Visualization Create a comprehensive mind map visualization for the Super Knowledge Base application based on the specification document. The mind map should show the main application architecture with these key nodes and their connections: Central Node: \"Super Knowledge Base\" Main Branches: 1. User Interface (with sub-nodes: Infinite Canvas, Search Interface, File Upload, Dashboard, Mobile App) 2. AI & ML Services (with sub-nodes: Content Analysis, Semantic Search, Knowledge Graph Generation, Memory System, Multi-modal Processing) 3. Data Management (with sub-nodes: PostgreSQL, Vector Database, File Storage, Backup Systems, Analytics) 4. Integrations (with sub-nodes: Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, Slack, Notion, GitHub, External APIs) 5. Security & Compliance (with sub-nodes: Authentication, Authorization, Encryption, Privacy Controls, Audit Logs) 6. Platform Features (with sub-nodes: Collaboration, Tagging System, Visual Mapping, Real-time Sync, Export/Import) Use different colors for each main branch, make the connections clear, and include icons or visual elements that represent each component. The mind map should be comprehensive but readable, showing the interconnected nature of all system components. Generated Images (3) Generated 9/17/2025, 10:17:36 PM Generated 9/17/2025, 10:17:36 PM Generated 9/17/2025, 10:17:36 PM File Changes (1) super_knowledge_base_mindmap.png /home/user/output/super_knowledge_base_mindmap.png Download 9/17/2025, 10:17:26 PM v1 image/png Notebook notebook_q3qWQ.ipynb notebook_q3qWQ.ipynb Download 4/15/2026, 12:30:01 PM v1 application/x-ipynb+json Perfect! Now let me create additional implementation documents to complete the specification. Let me create a detailed prompt creation document for the AI components and a technical requirements document. Using Tool | Doc Generate Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a comprehensive \"AI Prompt Engineering & Implementation Guide\" document as a companion to the main specification. This should include: 1. AI SYSTEM PROMPTS - Detailed prompts for content analysis, knowledge graph generation, semantic search, tagging, and memory systems 2. MULTI-MODAL PROCESSING SPECIFICATIONS - How to handle text, images, videos, audio, and documents 3. KNOWLEDGE GRAPH GENERATION ALGORITHMS - Step-by-step processes for creating relationships 4. SEMANTIC SEARCH IMPLEMENTATION - Vector embeddings, similarity calculations, and ranking 5. MEMORY SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE - Long-term context preservation and retrieval 6. AI INTEGRATION WORKFLOWS - How AI components work together 7. PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION - Caching strategies, batch processing, and cost management 8. TESTING & VALIDATION - Quality metrics and evaluation frameworks Make it technical and detailed enough for AI engineers to implement each component. Include specific prompts, algorithms, and code examples where appropriate. Format it professionally as an HTML technical document. Perfect! Now let me create one final knowledge base document that will serve as a master index for all the documentation created in this session: Using Tool | Doc Generate Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a \"Super Knowledge Base - Project Documentation Index\" that serves as the master knowledge base document tracking all the documentation and outputs created in this session. Include: 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW - Brief description of the Super Knowledge Base project 2. DOCUMENTATION INVENTORY - List of all documents created with descriptions and purposes 3. RESEARCH FINDINGS - Summary of key insights from analyzing Beluga.xyz, Constella.app, Everfind.ai, and Keymate.ai 4. FEATURE SYNTHESIS - Consolidated list of all features being integrated from the four platforms 5. VISUAL ASSETS - Reference to the mind map and any other visual materials 6. IMPLEMENTATION RESOURCES - Links to technical specifications, AI prompts, and implementation guides 7. DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP SUMMARY - Key milestones and timeline overview 8. TEAM RESOURCES - Quick reference for development team roles, budget, and requirements 9. NEXT STEPS - Immediate actions for starting development on EasySite.ai 10. APPENDICES - Additional resources, references, and supporting materials Format it as a comprehensive HTML knowledge base index that organizes all the work done and serves as the central hub for accessing all project documentation. Make it visually organized with clear sections and easy navigation. Excellent! I've successfully created a comprehensive Software Architecture & Specification document for your Super Knowledge Base application. Here's what I've delivered: 📋 Complete Documentation Package 1. Main Software Architecture & Specification Document Executive Summary & Product Vision - Clear project overview and value propositions Competitive Analysis - Detailed analysis of all four platforms (Beluga.xyz, Constella.app, Everfind.ai, Keymate.ai) Technical Architecture - Microservices, APIs, databases, and system design Core Feature Specifications - Multi-modal processing, AI search, visual mapping, collaboration UI/UX Guidelines - Interface design patterns and user experience requirements Security & Compliance - Authentication, encryption, privacy controls Implementation Roadmap - 12-month development phases with sprints and milestones Technical Stack - Recommended technologies for EasySite.ai platform Performance Requirements - Scalability targets and optimization strategies Deployment Specifications - Infrastructure and deployment configurations 2. AI Prompt Engineering & Implementation Guide System Prompts - Detailed prompts for content analysis, knowledge graph generation Multi-Modal Processing - Specifications for handling text, images, videos, audio Knowledge Graph Algorithms - Step-by-step relationship mapping processes Semantic Search Implementation - Vector embeddings and similarity calculations Memory System Architecture - Long-term context preservation strategies Performance Optimization - Caching, batch processing, cost management 3. Visual Mind Map A comprehensive visual representation showing: Central Hub: Super Knowledge Base 6 Main Branches: User Interface, AI & ML Services, Data Management, Integrations, Security & Compliance, Platform Features 31 Sub-components: All detailed features and capabilities Color-coded organization with icons for easy identification 4. Project Documentation Index A master knowledge base document that organizes all deliverables and serves as the central hub for accessing project resources. 🎯 Key Features Synthesized From the four platforms, I've integrated: From Beluga.xyz: AI-powered research assistance Specialized data sources access Productivity coaching capabilities From Constella.app: Visual infinite graph interface AI-powered smart retrieval Instant capture and connecting thoughts Zettelkasten methodology implementation From Everfind.ai: Universal workplace search Multi-app integration (Jira, Confluence, Google Workspace) Automatic document categorization AI assistant with citations From Keymate.ai: AI memory system with context preservation Multi-source content ingestion Structured memory organization Team collaboration features 💰 Implementation Overview Budget: $1.375M for Year 1 Timeline: 12 months in 4 phases Team: 7.5 FTE (Project Manager, 2 Frontend, 2 Backend, 1 AI/ML, 1 UI/UX, 0.5 DevOps, 1 QA) Platform: Optimized for EasySite.ai with microservices architecture 🚀 Ready for Development The specification is comprehensive enough for your development team to: Start immediately with Phase 1 foundation work Build incrementally following the detailed sprint planning Implement AI features using the provided prompts and algorithms Scale efficiently with the architectural guidelines Maintain quality through the testing and validation frameworks This documentation package provides everything needed to build your Super Knowledge Base on EasySite.ai, combining the innovation of all four platforms into one powerful, AI-driven knowledge management solution. Super Knowledge Base SAC Specification Click to open Edit in AI Docs Now let me create visual diagrams and charts to illustrate the system architecture and features: Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_mind_map {\"data\":{\"name\":\"Super Knowledge Base Platform\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Core Features\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"AI-Powered Search\"},{\"name\":\"Visual Mind Mapping Canvas\"},{\"name\":\"Multi-Modal Content Support\"},{\"name\":\"Intelligent Tagging System\"},{\"name\":\"Real-Time Collaboration\"},{\"name\":\"Auto-Organization\"}]},{\"name\":\"Content Types\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Text Documents\"},{\"name\":\"Images & Screenshots\"},{\"name\":\"Videos & Audio\"},{\"name\":\"PDFs & Presentations\"},{\"name\":\"Web Pages & URLs\"},{\"name\":\"Code Snippets\"}]},{\"name\":\"AI Capabilities\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Semantic Search\"},{\"name\":\"Auto-Summarization\"},{\"name\":\"Content Generation\"},{\"name\":\"Relationship Discovery\"},{\"name\":\"Smart Recommendations\"},{\"name\":\"Context Understanding\"}]},{\"name\":\"Integration Hub\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Google Workspace\"},{\"name\":\"Microsoft 365\"},{\"name\":\"Notion & Obsidian\"},{\"name\":\"Slack & Teams\"},{\"name\":\"GitHub & GitLab\"},{\"name\":\"Zapier & Webhooks\"}]},{\"name\":\"User Experience\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Infinite Canvas Interface\"},{\"name\":\"Mobile-First Design\"},{\"name\":\"Offline Capabilities\"},{\"name\":\"Voice Commands\"},{\"name\":\"Gesture Navigation\"},{\"name\":\"Customizable Workflows\"}]},{\"name\":\"Enterprise Features\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"SSO & Security\"},{\"name\":\"Team Management\"},{\"name\":\"Analytics Dashboard\"},{\"name\":\"API Access\"},{\"name\":\"Whi